 managers in key global locations. + Lead market and competitive analysis to support the targeted efforts of Product and Business Development teams. + Serve as the leader to build and execute internal and external communication plans including press, public relations, brand building and social media. + Build digital communication channels for clients, partners, developers, users and other internal and external community members. + Partner with Product and Business Development teams to plan, manage and execute marketing events including internal and external conferences and client/advisory groups. + Develop sales enablement tools, messaging, thought leadership and client/partner content to support business objectives. + Synthesize market developments to ensure internal teams are working on the right priorities to capitalize on market opportunities. + Collaborate closely with product, design and tech teams to translate market opportunities to value-based pricing models. + Contribute to the overall strategy, business focus and resource allocation decision making. + Own the long term success, including financial metrics and shareholder value of the new products and brands. Skills we are seeking + Ability to rapidly understand emerging technologies and business models and create intuitive, focused marketing plans and content. + Comfort operating in whitespace and an environment that requires a balance between risk taking and data-driven decision making. + Ability to attract and mange talent, be a persuasive leader in a high intensity environment. + Passion for creatively solving problems and an entrepreneurial spirit. Ability to adeptly pivot focus and resources based on new information and market forces. + Commercially-minded collaborator with a demonstrated ability to manage a large network of stakeholders. + Community builder who can understand the value drivers in multi-sided platforms. + Resourcefulness to execute an aggressive agenda with finite time and resources. + Strong communication and leaderships skills and ability to articulate views while building consensus. Professional experiences that will set you apart + 10+ years of marketing and/or strategy leadership experience within the financial services industry. Platform/network business experience a strong plus. + 5+ years' experience developing and launching marketing, PR, social media, sales collateral and communication plans for new product or business lines. + History of building and managing high performance marketing teams. + Management of UI/UX teams for B2B and/or marketplace products. + Prior leadership with crafting strategic positioning plans, brand pillars, brand beliefs and brand promises as well as the manifestation with brand symbols, wordmarks, etc. + Strong analytical and communication skills to build compelling business cases in order to win internal support for marketing initiatives + Ability to deliver clear, compelling and articulate written and verbal communications. + Experience with brand architecture decisions in the context of both large organizations and new products/businesses. + Knowledge of emerging financial services technologies. Specifically, blockchain and APIs as well as exposure to design-based thinking practices. + Exposure to international markets from a payments, markets, FX, supply chain and/or treasury standpoint. + Experience working in a fast-paced and highly cross-functional organization. + BA or BS required. MBA preferred JPMorgan Chase & Co., one of the oldest financial institutions, offers innovative financial solutions to millions of consumers, small businesses and many of the world's most prominent corporate, institutional and government clients under the J.P. Morgan and Chase brands. Our history spans over 200 years and today we are a leader in investment banking, consumer and small business banking, commercial banking, financial transaction processing and asset management. We recognize that our people are our strength and the diverse talents they bring to our global workforce are directly linked to our success. We are an equal opportunity employer and place a high value on diversity and inclusion at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of any protected attribute, including race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital or veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. In accordance with applicable law, we make reasonable accommodations for applicants' and employees' religious practices and beliefs, as well as any mental health or physical disability needs. Equal Opportunity Employer/Disability/Veterans ", 
